itemListElement.name: 3 Days in Olympic National Park from Seattle: Searching for Sasquatch

name: 3 Days in Olympic National Park from Seattle: Searching for Sasquatch
description: Like Sasquatch – 1,100 square mile Olympic National Park is gigantic, famous, and definitely elusive! Join our passionate naturalist guides (and Bigfoot!) on a quest to track down the wild essence of UNESCO World Heritage Site Olympic National Park.

review.name: Amazing tour
review.reviewBody:
I went on a three day trip. Emma was our guide. She made the whole trip really fun, peppering the drive with facts about the area, and podcasts about Sasquatch and the One Inch of Silence. Her camp cooking was excellent, and our beachside trailers were great and so cute. I really liked the environmental awareness of the trip.

The Hoh rainforest was wonderful, and we had the flexibility to go at our own pace, which I really enjoyed.

All six people on the trip were solo travellers, and we bonded really fast.

I highly recommend the trip!

itemListElement.name: Tacoma Narrows Bridge and War Memorial Park Walking Adventure-From Tacoma

name: Tacoma Narrows Bridge and War Memorial Park Walking Adventure-From Tacoma
description:
Walk more than one-mile across the Tacoma Narrows Bridge and experience firsthand the majestic Puget Sound from atop this amazing, man-made structure. 

 This road trip will first take you to the Narrows Bridge Museum in the small maritime city of Gig Harbor. Then you may stroll along Gig Harbor’s pleasant beach front through the Austin Estuary Park, ending at the amazing Beach Basket Souvenir Gift Shop.  

Lunch is just next door at the "Gourmet" Burger Shop, where you are sure to find something yummy to eat! 

 Our adventure continues to the Narrows Bridge Park, located on the shoreline of the Narrows Inlet where you will have a remarkable view of the entire bridge and be able to take amazing photographs from the Puget Sound shoreline.

 Next, you will be dropped off at the Scott Pierson Trail where you can begin your adventure across the bridge at your own pace, ending at the War Memorial Park in Tacoma.

itemListElement.name: BEST Mt. Rainier Full-Day Tour in Comfortable Van (Small Group)

name: BEST Mt. Rainier Full-Day Tour in Comfortable Van (Small Group)
description:
-Small group tour of one of the most visited mountains in the United States.
-Skip the crowded tour bus and ride in a comfortable, spacious van!
-Enjoy the smells of Evergreen Trees and learn why Washington is called 'The Evergreen State'
-Get many great selfies with Mt. Rainier!
-Enjoy connecting with nature as you meander through trails and forests in the park
-Plenty of rest stops on our way too and from Mt. Rainier National Park (4 total) for restroom, stretch and snack breaks.

name: Round the Sound
description: The Round the Sound bike experience is ideal for all levels of bike riders and shows the best scenery in the Puget Sound. The first part of the bike ride is flat, and on the Kitsap peninsula there are gentle hills, lots of downhills and coastal rides. Bike riders have the option of renting electric bikes, as well as hybrid and high quality road bikes. The scenery is mind blowing, and the combination of ferry rides, a beachfront park for lunch, and periodic stops allows bike riders to move at a comfortable pace. The best is that we don't return the way we came but always see something new and enjoy a beautiful ferry ride back to where we started. Everything is synchronized to the ferries, water taxis and allows time for a draft beer after the ride in Bremerton before heading back to Seattle.

name: Beautiful suite with bay views, includes shared hot tub and pool
description:
Newmark Tower Seattle Escape Suite

Our calendar is updated in real-time & our nightly rates are accurately displayed. Simply enter your desired dates and click 'Book Now!'

Come experience the height of Seattle luxury. Bringing modern relaxation to your urban getaway, the Seattle Escape Suite is a flawless retreat for all of your downtown adventures. Perfect for vacationers and business travelers, this newly designed and updated Newmark Tower Condominium with Puget Sound and Smith Tower views offers an open floor plan with fully equipped kitchen, two spacious bedrooms, and sleeps up to six guests. If you decide to book this marvelous retreat, you'll be granted access to the shared hot tub, fitness center, and indoor pool available!

With the waterfront, Seattle museums, shopping, and numerous cafes and restaurants at your doorstep, the options are endless. This unbeatable location is steps from Pike Place Market, Seattle Art Museum, Benaroya Hall, and many more! You can experience the Seattle scene and spend each night at a different local treasure! This gorgeous home away from home features a perfect Walk Score: 100!

Things to know:
Please note: Our Newmark Tower Condos require personal check-in service, a simple background check, and a legally required rental agreement.

Parking Notes: DIRECTIONS TO PARKING GARAGE FROM 1415 2nd Avenue:
Go South on 2nd to Union Avenue and turn Right.
Turn Right into the first driveway, the Target parking lot.
Pull up to first gate and locate the grey box mounted from the ceiling; hold access card up, through your windshield, facing the box and hold it until the light turns green and the gate opens. Make sure your vehicle is pulled up close enough to the gate/arm that the underground sensor is tripped by the vehicle. Proceed down to Level E and park in space 178.
This is the only authorized parking space for your use. Guests may use the Target public parking. This is a city style, underground parking structure best suited to small cars/smaller SUVs.  There is a posted sign for extremely low clearance at the entrance. Follow the Exit sign and the purple arrows to the vestibule for the elevator bay. Swipe access card next to grey box next to the door and enter. Take elevator to floor 17. Locate unit #1707. 

Please note: Take your access card with you whenever you leave the condo as you will need it to access various parts of the building. Also, if you were unable to provide vehicle information prior to your arrival, please either contact us or the Newmark Tower concierge with the following information: car make, model, year, color, and license number.

*The parking garage has a height restriction of 6'4" that includes a "no car-top carrier" provision. Please keep this in mind when arranging travel plans.

The Damage Waiver covers you for up to $2,000 of accidental damage to the Property or its contents (such as furniture, fixtures, and appliances) as long as you report the incident to the host prior to checking out. The Damage Waiver fee eliminates the need for a traditional security deposit.

review.name: Fun way to explore Seattle!
review.reviewBody: Debbie was amazing! A mix of Seattle history and delicious donuts. Debbie’s energy and her passion made it so much fun! Had a great day exploring Seattle!

review.name: Donut Dreams
review.reviewBody: We absolutely loved this tour! Our guide Amanda was the best and had so much insightful info. The donuts were all delicious!

review.name: Tasty donuts & fun tour!
review.reviewBody: The Underground Donut Tour was fun and the donuts were so tasty!  Our guide Holly kept us informed of interesting tidbits about Seattle history in general as well as about the shops we visited.

name: Politics - WA Legislative Building Tour
description:
Hotel, pier and airport pickup. 

One hour from Seattle, Olympia has a rich history as our State Capitol. Begin with a visit the Washington State Capitol Building. The Rotunda and Legislative Building are remarkable with every inch in beautiful granite. Inside you’ll also see the largest Tiffany chandelier collection in the world during your 50 minute tour.

You’ll dine in downtown historic Olympia. 

If interested you can visit a National Wildlife Refuge and walk the trails and boardwalks. This is located at the mouth of the Nisqually River where it meets Puget Sound saltwater.

Traveling in our comfortable company SUV, you’ll enjoy this getaway to historic Olympia. This a private tour for your party only, 2-5 guests.

review.name: Fantastic
review.reviewBody:
We've travel to other countries and the U.S., always found the trips to be more enjoyable with a local driver/guide.  Large groups on tour busses suck.  With Cheryl, we were treated like family, (the ones she loves).  I highly recommend booking her services which will lead to a wonderful, memorable experience.
We still keep in touch with her 3 years later from our home  in Florida.

name: All Inclusive Tulip Festival Package
description:
Tour Pick-up location: 1620 4th Ave. Seattle WA 98134

Upon arrival at the Washington State University Discovery Garden, your navigator and Master Gardener guide will meet you with refreshments and share an exclusive insider look at the WSU Discovery garden. Hop back on the coach as your expert horticulture guides take you touring around the local fields, sharing the region’s fascinating geology and tulip production history. Next stop, the famed Kiwanis Club Salmon BBQ, where you can taste the local flavor of alderwood grilled local salmon.* After lunch it’s off to Roozengaarde, owned by the Roozen family – bulb growers in Holland and the US since the early 1700s. Round out the day with a tour of Tulip Town, for more photo ops and a charming trolley tractor ride* for up-close viewing. Locals and tourists all agree our Tulip Festival Tour is a MUST for all PNW lovers.

*Kiwanis Club BBQ lunch and trolley tractor ride not included in basic tour price.

Note: No Tour Easter Sunday 4/12

itemListElement.name: Goat Yoga in Picturesque Snohomish, WA

name: Goat Yoga in Picturesque Snohomish, WA
description: Join us for two hours of bliss! The first hour you will be led through a yoga class by one of our certified yoga instructors while the goats meander around (and sometimes ON) you all the while perfecting your yoga technique. The second hour you are welcome to stay and spend time with the goats, giving them all the love they deserve. The goats love showing off their yoga moves and you will love spending time with them. You don't want to miss this absolutely amazing experience!

name: Zombie Scavengers Game - Seattle, WA
description:
CAN YOU SURVIVE THE ZOMBIE APOCALYPSE?

Zombie Scavengers leads you into the city to collect supplies to survive during this interactive scavenger game.

With the whole world in chaos and zombies outnumbering the living 10 to 1, small colonies of the living are doing all they can to survive. Using your smartphone, your team will be tasked with scavenging the city for food, supplies, weapons, and shelter. The more things you find, the more points you get and more likely you are to survive. Along the way, you will be asked to do a challenge or answer a trivia question in order to be rewarded virtual weapons to ward off the zombies. The area is crawling with relentless zombies, and rival colonies are moving in. If you get too relaxed, rival colonies will take what you worked hard to find. The goal is to find all of the items in hopes that you will survive the zombie apocalypse.
